    en: "WIC (Women, Infants, and Children) is a federal nutrition program for pregnant women, new mothers, infants, and children under 5. The application is shorter than most benefits applications but uses specific eligibility categories. This walkthrough explains what the WIC office asks at intake, what to bring, and how the eligibility check works at the appointment."
